race.comment: In a race smashed by scratchings HURSTVILLE ZAGREB (5) is a clear top pick. Started favourite when resuming over this course and distance last start but was no match for INNCOURT here last time out. That was his first run in four months so he should improve enough to take care of this field. FULL HAO (14) resumed last time out over 1300m at Rosehill and did a fair job to finish fourth. Progressive mare who won comfortably over the mile at Hawkesbury at the same stage last prep. Suited by the small field and with McDonald aboard is clearly the threat. COSMIC LAD (9) worked home well to finish runner-up here this distance last start, beating HURSTVILLE ZAGREB home. Has less improvement in him than Zagreb but should be competitive again. HEED THE OMENS (10) is back up from Victoria where he ran an eye-catcher at Moonee Valley most recently. In the mix on that form. ZENMASTER (7) impressed here last time and is open to further improvement at the third run back.
